üõí Blinkit Sales Data Analysis using Python
üìå Project Overview

This project focuses on analyzing Blinkit‚Äôs sales and customer dataset to uncover meaningful business insights. The objective was to perform data cleaning, exploratory data analysis (EDA), and visualization to identify revenue trends, customer behavior, and product performance.

The analysis helps understand sales patterns and supports data-driven decision-making.

üéØ Objectives

Clean and preprocess raw sales and customer data

Identify revenue trends and seasonal sales patterns

Analyze customer purchasing behavior

Determine top-performing products and categories

Generate actionable business insights using visualizations

üõ†Ô∏è Tools & Technologies Used

Python

Pandas ‚Äì Data cleaning & manipulation

NumPy ‚Äì Numerical operations

Matplotlib & Seaborn ‚Äì Data visualization

Jupyter Notebook ‚Äì Development environment

üìÇ Dataset Description

The dataset contains information related to:

Customer details

Product categories

Order quantity

Sales amount

Revenue

Outlet location and size

üîé Key Steps Performed
1Ô∏è‚É£ Data Cleaning & Preprocessing

Handled missing values

Removed duplicate records

Standardized column names

Converted data types for accurate analysis

2Ô∏è‚É£ Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Analyzed overall sales and revenue trends

Identified high-demand product categories

Studied customer purchasing patterns

Compared outlet performance by size and location

3Ô∏è‚É£ Data Aggregation

Used groupby() and pivot tables to summarize data

Performed category-wise and outlet-wise analysis

Calculated revenue contribution percentages

4Ô∏è‚É£ Data Visualization

Bar charts for category performance

Line plots for revenue trends

Pie charts for sales distribution

Heatmaps for correlation analysis

üìä Key Insights

Identified top-performing product categories contributing the highest revenue

Observed sales variation across outlet sizes and locations

Found patterns in customer purchase behavior

Highlighted revenue-driving products

üöÄ Business Impact

The analysis provides actionable insights that can help:

Improve inventory planning

Optimize product placement

Enhance marketing strategies

Increase overall revenue performance
